<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Female (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Length. 7.0 mm. Similar to male except for penultimate metasomal segment and sheath black, and genitalic characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="male">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Male.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Length. 5.0-8.0 mm. Antenna black, antennomeres 9-16 and sometimes 17 white. Head white with vertex and gena black, black extending anteriorly as V-shaped mark in front of ocelli; broad black median stripe on clypeus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Orthogonalys brevis, male paratype. 4 Head, front view. 5 Head, dorsal view. 6 Apex of abdomen and genitalia, lateral view. 7 Genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11358" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
). Mesosoma pale orange. Legs pale orange with hind tibia and tarsus darker to black. Wings hyaline, veins brown, costa more orange toward base; stigma brown to orange with anterior margin black. Genitalia brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="5" start="start">Antenna</pageBreakToken>
with 28 antennomeres. Head from above slightly concave behind, distance behind eyes about 0.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye length (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Orthogonalys brevis, male paratype. 4 Head, front view. 5 Head, dorsal view. 6 Apex of abdomen and genitalia, lateral view. 7 Genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11358" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Metascutellum broader than long, anterior breadth about 1.3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
medial length; metascutellum about 2.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Dorsum of mesosoma shiny, with widely spaced small punctures farther apart than 2-3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
puncture diameters. Propodeum coarsely reticulate (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia with paramere short, 1.6
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long, broadly rounded at apex, about 0.5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of gonostipes (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Orthogonalys brevis, male paratype. 4 Head, front view. 5 Head, dorsal view. 6 Apex of abdomen and genitalia, lateral view. 7 Genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11358" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
